-- Macquarie Rehires Hartt in Canada to Consult for Investment Bank
-- B y   S e a n   B .   P a s t e r n a k   a n d   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2013-02-13T11:50:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-12/macquarie-hires-hartt-in-canada-to-consult-for-investment-bank.html
Stanley Hartt , the former chairman
of  Macquarie Group Ltd .’s Canadian operations, has been retained
as a consultant for the firm’s investment bank.  Hartt, once chief of staff to former Canadian Prime
Minister  Brian Mulroney , signed a consulting agreement this week
with Macquarie Capital Markets (Canada), said  Aaron Boles , a
spokesman for the firm. Hartt stepped down as chairman at the
end of 2012, Boles said.  Hartt also agreed last month to join the Toronto office of
law firm  Norton Rose LLP .  To contact the reporters on this story:
